      "raw_text": "Corporation Counsel Hamblen, to\nwhom was referred the matter OF\napportioning the cost of the\nSprague st. tresle between the city,\nthe Traction and Inland Empire\ncompanies, has not reported yet,\nbut will in a few days. The con-\ntract which aggregates $500 will\nbe let to G. B. Dennis of the Ware\nhouse & Realty Co. His was the\nlowest bid. The board of works\nthe bid but the coun-\noil will not formally let 1t until\nit is known how much the street\nrailways are to pay."
